@startuml Data_Management_Filtering_Export
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title Data Management Filtering & Export Sequence

participant "User" as User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "app.js" as AppJS
participant "Firebase" as Firebase

User -> Browser: Navigate to "Data Management" page
activate Browser
Browser -> AppJS: Page switch event
deactivate Browser
activate AppJS
AppJS -> AppJS: bindDataManagementButtons()
deactivate AppJS

note over User,Browser: User sets filters
User -> Browser: Select date range\nFrom: 2025-01-01\nTo: 2025-01-20
User -> Browser: Select mode filter\n"periodic"
User -> Browser: Select status filter\n"success"
User -> Browser: Set temp range\nMin: 20, Max: 30
User -> Browser: Set humidity range\nMin: 50, Max: 80
User -> Browser: Select sort\n"time-desc"

User -> Browser: Click "Apply Filters"
activate Browser
Browser -> AppJS: Click event
deactivate Browser
activate AppJS

AppJS -> AppJS: Check isFirebaseConnected

alt Firebase Not Connected
    AppJS -> User: Show error\n"Firebase not connected"
else Firebase Connected
    AppJS -> AppJS: Read all filter inputs\ndateFrom, dateTo, mode, status,\ntempMin, tempMax, humiMin, humiMax, sortBy

    AppJS -> AppJS: Generate date range\ndates = []\nfor d = dateFrom to dateTo\ndates.push(YYYY-MM-DD)

    AppJS -> AppJS: addStatus("Loading filtered data...")

    loop For each date in range
        AppJS -> Firebase: firebase.ref('readings/{date}')\n.once('value')
        activate Firebase
        Firebase --> AppJS: Snapshot for date
        deactivate Firebase
        AppJS -> AppJS: Parse snapshot\nExtract records
    end

    AppJS -> AppJS: Merge all results\nallData = results.flat()

    AppJS -> AppJS: Apply mode filter\nif (mode && record.mode != mode) remove

    AppJS -> AppJS: Apply status filter\nif (status && record.status != status) remove

    AppJS -> AppJS: Apply temp range filter\nif (temp < min || temp > max) remove

    AppJS -> AppJS: Apply humidity range filter\nif (humi < min || humi > max) remove

    AppJS -> AppJS: Apply sorting\nSort by time/temp/humi\nasc or desc

    AppJS -> AppJS: Cache filtered data\nfilteredDataCache = filtered

    AppJS -> AppJS: renderDataManagementTable(filtered)

    AppJS -> Browser: Build HTML table\nFor each record:\n#, Date/Time, Temp, Humi, Mode, Status
    activate Browser
    deactivate Browser

    AppJS -> AppJS: updateDataStatistics(filtered)
    AppJS -> AppJS: Calculate:\n- Total records\n- Success rate\n- Avg temperature\n- Avg humidity

    AppJS -> Browser: Update #statsTotal\n#statsSuccess\n#statsAvgTemp\n#statsAvgHumi
    activate Browser
    deactivate Browser

    AppJS -> AppJS: addStatus("Loaded X records from Y total")

    AppJS -> User: Display filtered data
end
deactivate AppJS

note over User,Browser: User exports data
User -> Browser: Click "Export Filtered Data"
activate Browser
Browser -> AppJS: Click event
deactivate Browser
activate AppJS

AppJS -> AppJS: Check filteredDataCache length

alt No Data
    AppJS -> User: Show warning\n"No data to export"
else Has Data
    AppJS -> AppJS: Build CSV\nHeaders: #, Date, Time, Temp, Humi, Mode, Status, Sensor, Device

    loop For each record in filteredDataCache
        AppJS -> AppJS: Format row\nidx, date, time, temp, humi, mode, status, sensor, device
    end

    AppJS -> AppJS: Combine to CSV string\ncsv = headers + rows

    AppJS -> Browser: Create Blob(csv, "text/csv")
    activate Browser
    AppJS -> Browser: Create download link
    AppJS -> Browser: Trigger download\ndatalogger_export_{timestamp}.csv
    deactivate Browser

    AppJS -> AppJS: addStatus("Exported X records to CSV")
    AppJS -> User: File downloaded
end
deactivate AppJS

@enduml